flowRoot.flowPara: The raw source code for a page is written as plain text by their authors and are stored as such. They are sprinkled with formatting markers, but they have not yet been given their meaning.
The "tokenizer" reads the source code and gives meaning to each and every character. Formatting markers are tagged with their special meanings. The output is a list of all of the findings: "tokens".
The "treer" reads the tokens and puts them together using context. Random strings of words become paragraphs and so on. The database is used for image file data, page includes, and so on as well.
The "HTML Converter" takes the output from the "Treer" and directly converts it into HTML source code; all the data needed to construct a complete page is contained within the "page tree".
Because the "page tree" is well structured and is available as a direct "JSON" output, a relatively simple program can convert it into any format desirable.
